description:
Adrian is an Information Systems Professional with more than 30 years experience in Information Technology. He had demonstrated ability to achieve results, both individually and through a team environment.

Adrian currently is a Senior Technology Specialist of the Network Architecture group at AT&T Global Network Services. His recent work includes:
•	Designing and implementing F5 LTM & GTM in Amazon Web Services environment;
•	Designing and implementing F5 LTM & APM and Blue Coat Virtual Secure Web Gateway in CSC CloudCompute® environment;
•	Designing and implementing F5 LTM & APM for Sharepoint, MS Exchange Client Access Server, migrating from MS Threat Management Gateway (TMG) server;
•	Designing and implementing F5 LTM for MS Lync server;
•	Designing and implementing Enhanced Load Balancing Service using F5 LTM and APM technology;
•	Developing Managed SSL VPN & Load Balancing Services using F5 LTM, GTM & APM;
•	Developing Managed WAN Optimisation Service using Riverbed Steelhead devices;
•	Investigating voice and data network performance problem of a satellite link at a remote mine site in North Queensland;
•	Designing and implementing the Communication Infrastructure for the Smart Meters Deployment at one of power distribution company in Victoria;
•	Developing the next generation of Network Application Management (NAM) services and Web Acceleration Management (WAM) services;
•	Designing, and implementing Server Load Balancing and Web Acceleration Services for Documentum, SAP Portal, Link One and various Microsoft .NET Applications.

Specialties: Bandwidth Management, WAN Optimisation, Web Acceleration, Application Performance Management, Layer 4 & Layer 7 Server Load Balancing, Remote Office Communications, Satellite Communication (VSAT) Technologies.

